'''Guardian Squadron''' was one of the three [[BTL Y-wing starfighter/Legends|Y-wing]] [[Squadron/Legends|squadrons]] that made up [[Defender Wing]]. The other two were [[Champion Squadron|Champion]] and [[Warden Squadron|Warden]] Squadrons.

Guardian Squadron was under the personal command of [[General/Legends|General]] [[Horton Salm/Legends|Horton Salm]]. The Squadron took part in the failed attack on [[Borleias/Legends|Borleias]] [[6 ABY/Legends|six and a half years]] after the [[Battle of Yavin/Legends|Battle of Yavin]]. [[Defender Wing]] was instrumental in saving [[Rogue Squadron/Legends|Rogue Squadron]] from certain destruction during the assault.

Defender Wing fought in the [[Yag'Dhul system/Legends|Yag'Dhul system]], again with Rogue Squadron, in order to capture a supply of [[Bacta/Legends|bacta]] during the [[Bacta War]].

At some point during the Galactic Civil War, Guardian Squadron was equipped with [[BTL-S8 K-wing assault starfighter]]s.

During the [[Thrawn campaign|Thrawn Crisis]], Guardian was reequipped with [[A/SF-01 B-wing starfighter/Legends|B-wings]] and subsequently took part in the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic's]] campaign against the rogue [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] [[Admiral/Legends|Admiral]] [[Delak Krennel]].

